fields.bio: Web development is a field where I can put my love for problem-solving, collaboration, and logic to good use. I have high standards for myself and my work, and I'm excited to continue learning and improving upon my code.
fields.project_detail: Single-page application built with React that allows the user to organize their personal knitting supplies, patterns, and knitting projects as well as upload photos of finished projects to a gallery.

fields.bio: I built a portfolio site and that was the moment I realized I really enjoy and thrive in web design and development. From that point on I dedicated my time to learning new skills.
fields.project_detail: Hold My Color is a web app where a user not only builds their color palette for their next project, but can download it in a SASS file or create their style guide as a GitHub Issue.

fields.bio: I love to make cool things that make life easier for me and everyone else. Things that get business done and make productivity soar. I speak fluent web stack, including HTML, JavaScript, CSS, Bootstrap, React and Python
fields.project_detail: A mobile app that lets parents and kids manage money together. Parents can add funds and chores to kid accounts. Kids can accept chores to earn money and buy items on their wish list with parents approval.

fields.bio: Since I was a child I had a passion for technology. The first computer I had was Sinclair ZX81. That's where I started my journey on technology and my passion to learn. When I was 13 the first language I did was BASIC.
fields.project_detail: You will be able to track your player from the MANCHESTER UNITED TEAM, and you also Add Delete and Update them. This app was built with HTML, JavaScript, React, SCSS.
